content: Yes but the spots are currently at capacity at the moment.
Will there be any future need?
I have a lot of experience
Maybe later it depends on signups.
So what do I do?
Wait till you're able to sign up. In the meantime we make a lot of calls per day. You can find that info in <#1242256751445934262>
How will I know if there are future opportunities to sign up to text?
You can keep on checking this link https://events.democrats.org/event/654680/ We don't really now when spots opens up or someone takes them.
Ok thanks. Good luck!
Hi <@1278148917376061543> New link is here -- training times have opened up https://events.democrats.org/event/672393/
I signed up for the zoom today and the link didn‚Äôt work

Hi <@1278148917376061543> Sorry to hear! You do need to be logged into a Zoom account before joining the meeting - or if you click the link, it'll prompt you to sign up for a Zoom account (or log in). Was that the error you were seeing?
Yes
Understood - sorry for the confusion! That is required for these Zoom trainings -- and I've sent feedback to staff to see if we can make that more clear in the confirmation emails.
You can sign up for another training at the same link - and I would suggest logging in a few minutes early to make sure you are logged into the zoom account.
